en.answer: During a turn in which the effect of Super Rush Headlong was applied, if the targeted monster battles with a monster that is unaffected by Spell Cards, the opponent's monster is not destroyed and Damage Calculation is performed normally.
en.question: If a monster targeted for the effect of Super Rush Headlong attacks a monster affected by Forbidden Lance, what happens with the effect of Super Rush Headlong?
en.title: If a monster targeted for the effect of Super Rush Headlong attacks a monster affected by Forbidden Lance, what happens with the effect of Super Rush Headlong?

ja.answer: 「<<12010>>」の効果が適用されているターン、対象のモンスターと戦闘を行った相手モンスターが魔法カードの効果を受けない場合には、相手モンスターは破壊されず、通常通りのダメージ計算が行われます。
